Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.83,0:00:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The dreams embraced by a single life{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.84,0:00:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}are boundless beyond even the stars.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.84,0:00:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The dreams that we foster over time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.85,0:00:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}are waiting for the moment\N{\c&He1e1e1&}when we come upon them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.53,0:00:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The words we exchange\N{\c&He1e1e1&}make our hearts tremble,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.53,0:00:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}and a chance meeting\N{\c&He1e1e1&}could change the future.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.21,0:01:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}People, no matter who they are,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}as they pursue their dreams,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.48,0:01:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}have the courage to travel new paths.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.15,0:01:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}As we leave behind a living\N{\c&He1e1e1&}testament of our journey,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.49,0:01:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}the Galaxy Railways on which\N{\c&He1e1e1&}we travel continue ever on.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.53,0:02:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}When a grain of wheat falls to earth,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}does anyone hear the sound it makes?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.21,0:02:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}When the wheat produces a bounty of grain,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that is when people first realize...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.55,0:02:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}...the true value of a grain of wheat.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.22,0:02:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}"Afterglow"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.90,0:02:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.57,0:02:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, Tenderfoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.57,0:02:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yes!?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.91,0:02:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You sure are getting cozy, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.91,0:02:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm finished doing the maintenance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.25,0:02:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}These aren't tight enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.92,0:02:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What are you looking at?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.25,0:02:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Nothing much...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.59,0:02:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you've got time to stare at my face,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you've got time to tighten the other nuts!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.92,0:02:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Do the whole train over again!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.59,0:02:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That SDF boy is getting it\N{\c&He1e1e1&}right off the bat, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.26,0:03:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I hear he's undergoing re-training.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I guess he hasn't been making the grade.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.87,0:03:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Well, it does a person good\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to come here at least once
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.17,0:03:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and have Old Man Whitman\N{\c&He1e1e1&}get angry at them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.21,0:03:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Especially youngsters like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.41,0:03:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Standing guard on the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}rich man's train, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.76,0:03:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}I wonder how Yuuki-kun is doing...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.10,0:03:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}SDF!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.76,0:03:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}How cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.77,0:03:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Little boy... have you gotten lost?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Where's your mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.77,0:03:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Charlie!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.77,0:03:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Pegasus Express No. 227, bound for\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Rosamund will be departing shortly...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.78,0:03:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Mama!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.78,0:03:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Watch yourself, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.78,0:03:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Those who are boarding, please hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.39,0:04:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Pegasus, so beautiful,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}as you gallop through the skies...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.40,0:04:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yet shall your wings be broken,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and yourself covered in dirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.74,0:04:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All of them, he says. How many\N{\c&He1e1e1&}of these does he think there are?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.75,0:04:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Here, here, and here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.09,0:04:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Listen, each train has its own quirks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.42,0:04:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You have to know where\N{\c&He1e1e1&}they tend to come loose,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.62,0:04:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}or you're no good as a maintenance worker.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.43,0:04:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Until you learn, you'll just\N{\c&He1e1e1&}have to do them all, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.76,0:04:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm just here to study and train.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.77,0:04:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Oh? So the tenderfoots these days are\N{\c&He1e1e1&}starting to talk back like this now,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.74,0:04:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.10,0:04:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Whitman, I have a name... Yuuki Manabu!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.78,0:05:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You can't serve in the SDF\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and not know anything about trains.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.15,0:05:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Am I wrong, Tenderfoot?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.38,0:05:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Enough already. You bother me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.40,0:05:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hurry up and get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.41,0:05:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This just isn't my day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.41,0:05:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So what about the nuts?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I know about them!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.08,0:05:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.75,0:05:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Incredible!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.09,0:05:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}They're scrapping this car, too?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}It's a pretty old model.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.76,0:05:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's bolted together nice and tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.44,0:06:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What did you do that for!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.70,0:06:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Do not touch this with your filthy hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.37,0:06:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I was just looking at it, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.04,0:06:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What can you tell just by looking?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.04,0:06:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Now you're going to lecture me\N{\c&He1e1e1&}about junkyard cars!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.85,0:06:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's just going to get\N{\c&He1e1e1&}scrapped anyway, right!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.38,0:06:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What is it with you!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.72,0:06:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you've got a problem with me,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}then come out and say it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.39,0:06:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Come with me. I've got\N{\c&He1e1e1&}something to say to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.73,0:06:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I've had enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.74,0:06:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Judging by the look on your face,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}he really let you have it, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.41,0:06:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.41,0:06:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You must have touched {\i1}No. 825{\i0}.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.09,0:06:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That train is the old-timer's treasure,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.09,0:06:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}When the old-timer became a mechanic,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.43,0:06:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}it was the first train\N{\c&He1e1e1&}he was put in charge of.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.43,0:07:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He beamed just as brightly\N{\c&He1e1e1&}as those cars did. But then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.70,0:07:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}...who could have known ahead of time\N{\c&He1e1e1&}about the destruction of Planet Rosamund?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.37,0:07:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.38,0:07:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It was a disaster that\N{\c&He1e1e1&}destroyed half the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.05,0:07:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}At the time, the old man was\N{\c&He1e1e1&}heading back to Destiny on {\i1}No. 825{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.75,0:07:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}loaded with magnetic ore.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.39,0:07:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Rosamund Station, the mine,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and the old man's house
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.50,0:07:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}were on the chunk\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that got blown away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.74,0:07:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Many people perished,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}including his parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.41,0:07:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}his younger sister,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.11,0:07:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and all the people from the town\N{\c&He1e1e1&}where he was born and raised.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.08,0:07:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Rosamund Mine was shut down,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and the old man was stationed here,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.95,0:07:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}at Headquarters' maintenance department.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.09,0:08:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Ever since then,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}he's been looking after {\i1}No. 825{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.59,0:08:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}making sure she can take off at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.36,0:08:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But tomorrow is her last day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.70,0:08:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}She's going to be junked tomorrow,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}at that same scrap yard you were at.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.37,0:08:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Watch what you say around him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.50,0:08:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The old man can't stand it\N{\c&He1e1e1&}when people talk about the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.73,0:08:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is a message from\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the Pegasus Express...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.40,0:08:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The train is now entering Planet\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Rosamund's scenic Water Harp Caverns.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.41,0:08:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Previously, this was a mine\N{\c&He1e1e1&}for unique magnetic ores.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.74,0:08:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please enjoy the mystical music woven\N{\c&He1e1e1&}by the magnetically charged ores
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.01,0:09:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and the falling droplets of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.36,0:09:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What was that just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.03,0:09:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The magnetic shields have failed!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.04,0:09:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Mama!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.71,0:09:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are we okay now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.38,0:09:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please remain calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.05,0:09:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We are currently conducting an\N{\c&He1e1e1&}inspection to ensure our safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.39,0:09:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please wait shortly until\N{\c&He1e1e1&}we get underway again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.72,0:09:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is the {\i1}Pegasus Express{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.06,0:09:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We have encountered a magnetic cascade\N{\c&He1e1e1&}within Planet Rosamund's view point,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.46,0:09:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and are unable to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.40,0:09:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Request immediate assistance!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.08,0:10:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Receiving an emergency transmission\N{\c&He1e1e1&}from the {\i1}Pegasus Express{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.65,0:10:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}They are unable to move!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I can't contact them!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.09,0:10:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Send Sirius Platoon at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.76,0:10:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.76,0:10:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}A magnetic cascade has occurred\N{\c&He1e1e1&}within Planet Rosamund's view point.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.09,0:10:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sirius Platoon, mobilize at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.10,0:10:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Go and rescue the {\i1}Pegasus Express{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.43,0:10:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Rosamund?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.10,0:10:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Repeat... a magnetic cascade has occurred\N{\c&He1e1e1&}within Planet Rosamund's view point.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.77,0:10:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sirius Platoon, mobilize at once.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Go and rescue the {\i1}Pegasus Express{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.78,0:10:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Systems all green!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.45,0:10:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Big One{\i0}, move out!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.07,0:11:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Where's Whitman!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.07,0:11:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Beats me. Probably with his partner,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.41,0:11:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Electrical systems check out...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.75,0:11:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Power systems check out...\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Magnetic shield checks out...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.75,0:11:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Audrey...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.76,0:11:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Okay then, let's do it, partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.09,0:11:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Old-timer!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.43,0:11:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Old-timer!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.10,0:11:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is Headquarters. No. 825\N{\c&He1e1e1&}has not been cleared to depart.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.01,0:11:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please come to a halt at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.11,0:11:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Repeat... No. 825 has not\N{\c&He1e1e1&}been cleared to depart.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.78,0:11:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}-- Old-timer!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}-- Please come to a halt at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.45,0:11:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.45,0:11:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Old-timer...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.13,0:12:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The inside of the Water Harp Caverns\N{\c&He1e1e1&}is like an ants' nest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.60,0:12:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The {\i1}Pegasus Express{\i0}'\N{\c&He1e1e1&}current position is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.07,0:12:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Their location is exactly 1/8 of the way\N{\c&He1e1e1&}through the total length of 82 kilos.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.40,0:12:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We will go through Point A. F and\N{\c&He1e1e1&}then head toward them to rescue them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.08,0:12:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is bad. The electrical systems\N{\c&He1e1e1&}have become unstable.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.75,0:12:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are we okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.08,0:12:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Depends on how long\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Big One{\i0}'s shields hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.75,0:12:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't worry. If we have to,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.09,0:12:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}we can blow a hole through the guts\N{\c&He1e1e1&}of the cavern and rescue them that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.77,0:12:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Still unable to contact {\i1}Pegasus Express{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.77,0:12:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Our quarry is in sight. All we have\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to do now is take them back with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.44,0:12:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.78,0:12:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What is it, Louis?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.11,0:12:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm unable to monitor any sounds\N{\c&He1e1e1&}coming from the Water Harp Caverns.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.78,0:12:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sounds?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.45,0:12:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's too quiet...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.41,0:13:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain! The {\i1}Pegasus Express{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.75,0:13:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Our magnetic shield has failed!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.75,0:13:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The main control system is down!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.42,0:13:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Get us through here one way or another!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.76,0:13:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.76,0:13:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Our drive systems are down!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.10,0:13:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.77,0:13:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll do it manually.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.77,0:13:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bruce!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.77,0:13:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Damn, it's no use!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.11,0:13:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Pegasus Express{\i0}' drive speed\N{\c&He1e1e1&}is increasing to its limits.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.81,0:14:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The effects of the magnetic storm\N{\c&He1e1e1&}have probably made it a runaway.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.38,0:14:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What about {\i1}Big One{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.38,0:14:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Contact with them has been broken off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.72,0:14:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Old-timer, the {\i1}Pegasus Express{\i0}...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.06,0:14:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.39,0:14:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}A- a- amazing acceleration!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.06,0:14:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This freight train was designed to haul\N{\c&He1e1e1&}a full cargo of Rosamund's magnetic ores.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.40,0:14:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But now, we've got no cargo cars,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and its load is no more than two people.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.74,0:14:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But it's going to be\N{\c&He1e1e1&}scrapped tomorrow, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.74,0:14:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Who told you that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.41,0:14:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Uh, Akatsuki-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.75,0:14:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}For pete's sake,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}why did he have to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.75,0:14:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.76,0:14:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.76,0:14:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.77,0:14:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That bastard...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.77,0:15:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Tenderfoot, why did you come with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.44,0:15:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why, you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.04,0:15:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Do you need a reason to help others?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.38,0:15:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Old-timer, doesn't that go for you, too?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I mean, you're a mechanic,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.88,0:15:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and yet you're operating this thing,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.72,0:15:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's the job of the SDF to help people.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.06,0:15:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm sorry about giving you\N{\c&He1e1e1&}nothing but backtalk.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.07,0:15:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Tenderfoot, those are\N{\c&He1e1e1&}admirable words, there!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.74,0:15:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Get down!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.08,0:15:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Relax, Tenderfoot! We still\N{\c&He1e1e1&}have our magnetic shields!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.76,0:15:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.76,0:15:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We got passed up by {\i1}No. 825{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.09,0:15:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.43,0:15:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}How is the drive system?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.43,0:15:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That will still take some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.38,0:16:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's okay, Mama. The SDF\N{\c&He1e1e1&}will come and help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.05,0:16:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is bad. There's a\N{\c&He1e1e1&}magnetic storm ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.72,0:16:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}When will systems be restored?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.39,0:16:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I've finished reinstalling\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the drive program.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.66,0:16:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sub-control systems are unaffected.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.73,0:16:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We can get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.73,0:16:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All right, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.39,0:16:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.73,0:16:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki, save the Old-timer.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.40,0:16:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Old-timer! Snap to!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.41,0:16:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.74,0:16:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll take over. Old-timer,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you get some rest!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.08,0:16:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Rosamund is the devil's own den.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I can't leave this up to a tenderfoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.42,0:16:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Well then, direct me!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}That will be good enough, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.76,0:16:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Who's in the picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.43,0:17:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Didn't you hear? I wasn't able\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to save them... any of them...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.70,0:17:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Not a single one of them...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.04,0:17:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We have to rescue the {\i1}Pegasus Express{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&}before the next magnetic storm hits.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.38,0:17:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.38,0:17:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.71,0:17:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The destruction from the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}magnetic storm is spreading.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.58,0:17:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's only a matter of time before\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Planet Rosamund is destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.39,0:17:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We still have {\i1}No. 825{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.73,0:17:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I see it! The {\i1}Pegasus Express{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.40,0:17:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All right, let's do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.06,0:17:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Tenderfoot, are you ready for this!?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.73,0:17:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.40,0:17:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's no use! I've got no choice\N{\c&He1e1e1&}but to cut the passenger cars loose!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.74,0:17:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.41,0:17:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is the Rosamund Mine\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Freight Train {\i1}No. 825{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.98,0:17:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We've just caught up with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.75,0:17:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We're going to start pulling\N{\c&He1e1e1&}on you via your coupling unit!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.75,0:17:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}No. 825{\i0}!?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.36,0:18:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Once the arms are extended,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.70,0:18:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}pull the lever at your feet!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}The operating lever will come out,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.70,0:18:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and then it's all up to your timing.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}It's up to you now, Tenderfoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.38,0:18:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.71,0:18:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't rush it. There's still time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.72,0:18:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Listen to the song of the engine\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and match your timing with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.39,0:18:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Song of the engine?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.39,0:18:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's right. The song I've been\N{\c&He1e1e1&}listening to ever since I was a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.06,0:18:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}They've caught up, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.73,0:18:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We can do this! Full speed, David!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.73,0:18:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.40,0:18:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.74,0:18:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It engaged!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.74,0:18:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.07,0:18:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I've put it in reverse!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Get back here, Tenderfoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.08,0:18:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.70,0:19:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Old-timer!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.03,0:19:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Old-timer!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.37,0:19:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Old-timer!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.70,0:19:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You did well, Partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.05,0:19:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Old-timer...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.71,0:19:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is {\i1}Big One{\i0}. The magnetic storm's\N{\c&He1e1e1&}destruction is increasing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.95,0:19:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Do not alter speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.39,0:19:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We'll hook up and flee\N{\c&He1e1e1&}from Rosamund together.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.72,0:19:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain! The old-timer!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.06,0:19:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki, is that you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.39,0:19:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please help the old-timer!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.39,0:19:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Somebody, help the old-timer!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Help the old-timer!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.73,0:19:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.11,0:20:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Old-timer...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.11,0:20:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, Tenderfoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.78,0:20:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's what the old-timer\N{\c&He1e1e1&}would be saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.78,0:20:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The old-timer had a bad heart.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}He said when he died,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.45,0:20:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}he wanted to be listening to the song\N{\c&He1e1e1&}of the engine while next to this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.12,0:20:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Looks like he got his wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.46,0:20:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I also heard her song.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.13,0:21:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}She had a stubborn, powerful voice,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}just like you did, Old-timer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.74,0:21:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Ah! It's the {\i1}No. 825{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.74,0:21:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}A grain of wheat...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.75,0:21:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}You never know whether its life will have\N{\c&He1e1e1&}had any value until the very last moment.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.75,0:21:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}However, its memory will\N{\c&He1e1e1&}take root in people's hearts,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.79,0:21:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}and in time, produce a bountiful harvest.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.37,0:21:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}How many nights have I\N{\c&He1e1e1&}spent alone since then?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.38,0:22:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Constantly having dreams of the hope\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that you are, as I lightly sleep.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.06,0:22:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The smiles and tears that\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you gave to me and me alone{\i0}
